Draft character-arc metadata: how each entity below CHANGES across the story.
The prose writer (a later stage) reads this per passage as "who this entity is
right now, and where they are heading" — it is what lets a scene foreground ONE
aspect of a character instead of restating every known fact. It is never shown
to the player.

